## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- ***Using 2 pointers approach***.
- ***i*** will iterate over all elements & ***j*** will be the index off duplicates numbers.
- We will replace ***j*** only if we find a number not similar to the j-indexed number.
- Increase the value of the unique element every time j increased.
- Edge case: if you return 0 while n=0, it will give a run time error.
- **Time complexity:** O(n).

### Solution 02

- ***This uses extra space, which doesn’t satisfy the condition of the question.***
- First, we put all the elements in a set & only unique elements will be stored.
- Calculate the size of the set & iterate all elements of nums and replace them with set values.
- **Time complexity:** O(n).

