solutions.content:
The Objective of the problem is to move all the non duplicates to the front of the Array
Giving that the Array is on Ascending order, taking it to the advantage to solve the problem

Using two pointer algorithm
Where pointer
```x```  -  keeps track of **next** non duplicate to handle 
```y```  - runs throught the array in search of next non duplicate to replace in place of pointer ```x```

since its an ascending array, the search criteria is number should be greater than the previous non duplicate(```x-1```)

Once we found the next non duplicate number replace in place of ```x``` and continue the search until array ends

Return ```x``` though it is incremented at the end, since we start ```x``` pointer from 1 considering the index 0 contains the first non duplicate number and array size is minimum 1.

```class Solution {
    public int removeDuplicates(int[] nums) {

        int x=1;

        for(int y=x ; y < nums.length; y++)
        {
            if(nums[y] > nums[x-1])
            {
                nums[x++]=nums[y];
            }
        }
        return x;
    }
}

