C++ has STL function **unique( )** which removes all consecutive duplicates. You can use it to complete the program in 2 lines.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int removeDuplicates(vector<int>& nums) {
        int idx = unique(nums.begin(), nums.end()) - nums.begin();
        return idx;
    }
};
```
